{% call components.section("Pattern 1: Modal") -%}

  <p>A modal personalization is an introduction of a notice that sits on top of the page and fades back all content below. This is a <strong>priority 1</strong> implementation, as it prevents a user from interacting with the rest of the interface.</p>

  <h3>Design</h3>

  <p>Modal can be used on both desktop and mobile.</p>

    <div class="inline-flex centered margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/modal/modal.svg' | url }}" alt="Modal" style="">
    </div>

  <h3>How to use</h3>

  <ol>
    <li>Use sparingly as it interrupts the user workflow, requiring immediate attention and taking them away from their current task.</li>
    <li>Best practice is to trigger a modal when the user interacts with an element. For instance, show it if the user selects something. If that’s not possible, show it once a user has completed a task.</li>
    <li>Refrain from presenting a modal while the user is likely to be in the middle of a task.</li>
    <li>Per our design system, every modal should include a close button. It should also close when a user clicks out  of the modal, and when the keyboard esc button is pressed.</li>
    <li>Messaging should be simple within a modal: don’t include multiple steps or long forms.</li>
    <li>Modal can be used on mobile, but consider that it could be harder to close a modal on a smaller screen.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>The audience</h3>

  <p>A modal can be used for the following types of content (among others):</p>
  
  <ol>
    <li>Product announcements</li>
    <li>Notifications related to previous user action</li>
    <li>An experience that ideally doesn't migrate a user away from a page</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Existing optimizations</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>SOLP Thank you recommendations (upcoming, see XD)</li>
    <li>Marketable contacts project (upcoming, see XD)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Get started with the modal</h3>

  <ol>
    <li>Evaluate your need against the details above</li>
    <li>Review the testing links to see prior use cases</li>
    <li>Mock up your idea in context using the modal pattern in Adobe XD</li>
    <li>Submit questions concerning user experience to the Digital Systems UX team: digital-systems-web-team@redhat.com </li>
  </ol>

{%- endcall %}

