{% call components.section("Pattern 2: Sticky banner") -%}

  <p>The sticky banner experience represents a way to provide a user with a secondary offer without interrupting their experience. The banner sticks to the bottom of the screen, and overlays existing content.</p>

  <h3>Design</h3>

    <ol>
      <li>For banners that link to a set of assets like in Pathfactory, the image shown above has been used to describe what the user gets.</li>
      <li>For banners that link to specific assets, a resource icon can be used in place of the Pathfactory image. See the XD mockup and a list of Icons for resources.</li>
      <li>The headline should not wrap. 35-42 characters or under should be safe.</li>
      <li>The supporting text should not wrap to more than 2 lines. 85-110 characters, depending on how the first row wraps, should be safe.</li>
      <li>Visitors should be able to permanently close the banner—the same banner should not pop back up upon their next visit.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="inline-flex centered margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/sticky-banner/sticky-banner.svg' | url }}" alt="Sticky banner" style="">
    </div>

  <h3>How to use</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>The banner animates in from the bottom of the page. We often require that the visitor scroll past the fold before revealing the banner to avoid interfering with the page’s hero messaging.</li>
    <li>Decide on which pages to show the banner. We typically do not show a banner on landing pages like the Solutions pages, and thought leadership articles. See the global activity exclude list for redhat.com.</li>
    <li>Design the banner to explicitly tell the visitor what they’ll get if they click. For instance, use an image that visually describes the resource, write the description and CTA to be specific to the resource.</li>
    <li>The Drift chatbot will appear in front of the banner as an icon—minimal conflict.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The audience</h3>
  
  <ul>
    <li>This banner can be displayed to site visitors who have shown interest in a product or topic, but have not converted.</li>
    <li>We recommend the audience be large enough so that a clickthrough rate of under 10% is sufficient to meet goals.</li>
    <li>Expect a fairly high close rate, based on initial trials, in the 40% range.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Existing optimizations</h3>

  <h4><a href="#">Hybrid cloud experience</a> (open in incognito mode, close cookie banner, refresh page)</h4>
  <p><strong>Goal</strong>: Surface gated, high-value hybrid cloud theme content to visitors who have recently shown interest in the hybrid cloud topic via browsing behavior, but refrained from form conversion in these visits.</p>

  <h4>Cloud-native development, <a href="#">Experience</a> | <a href="#">Deck</a></h4>
  <p><strong>Goal</strong>: Surface gated, high-value cloud native app dev theme content to visitors who have recently shown interest in the cloud-native dev topic via browsing behavior, but refrained from form conversion in these visits.</p>

