{% call components.section("Pattern 4: Announcement banner") -%}

  <p>The announcement banner pattern is a <strong>priority 1</strong> personalization and should be used sparingly. This pattern places a skinny banner at the very top of the site, showing prominence over the navigation.</p>

  <h3>Design</h3>

    <p>Use the announcement banner pattern to display an important message at the top of the site. The banner can exist on one or more pages. The placement can either have a themed background image or a solid color background. To use colored backgrounds, use alert color styles.</p>

    <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/announcement/announcement-sample-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Announcement banner" style="border:1px solid #d2d2d2;">
    </div>

  <h3>How to use</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>If there's a logo associated with the announcement, create it at max width 80px</li>
    <li>Provide a headline/description of the announcement. This text should be no longer than 60 characters</li>
    <li>Provide a call to action. The text for the CTA should be around 25 characters.</li>
    <li>Provide the link to the announcement if applicable.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The audience</h3>

  <p>An alert banner can be used for the following types of content (among others):</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Important cross-site announcements</strong>: top-tier press releases, company announcements, important product launches. Use a red background.</li>
    <li>Single page alerts related to a global announcement or important in-page content.</li>
  </ul>


  <h3>Get started with the announcement banner</h3>

  <ol>
    <li>Establish your target audience and the pages you’d want the target audience to respond on.</li>
    <li>Define the offer you’re trying to promote (event, webinar, announcement, press release).</li>
    <li>Create the logo or small image associated with the alert if needed</li>
    <li>Create the headline/description</li>
    <li>Create the call to action and define the link</li>
    <li>Mock up your idea in context using the announcement bar pattern in Adobe XD</li>
    <li>Submit questions concerning user experience to the Digital Systems UX team: digital-systems-web-team@redhat.com</li>
  </ol>

