{% call components.section("Pattern 7: Inline alert") -%}

  <p>The inline alert pattern is a single or multiple page offer that appears inline with the page content.</p>

  <h3>Design</h3>

    <p>This pattern only accepts copy, no imagery. It can accommodate a single link to another location or two links. One option is to use yes | no. If “no” is selected another message will be shown:</p>

    <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/alert/alert-usage-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Alert" style="--inline-img-max-width: 340px;">
    </div>

    <p>If the visitor selects “no” consider if or when the alert should be shown again for the same visitor. It could be suppressed for a week, a month or forever depending on the goal of the project.</p>

    <p>The alert pattern in Adobe XD has two styles per alert type. Either can be used.</p>

  <h3>How to use</h3>

  <ol>
    <li>Use when the goal is to show a message pertinent to the surrounding content.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>The audience</h3>

  <p>This card can be displayed to any appropriate audience group.</p>

